{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566513","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566513"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:43:26+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:43:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18839"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18839","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18839"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.48,0.38,0.06,0.07,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11572"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79657"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11572","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11572"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18839"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64961"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"4958"},{"type":"tags","id":"4986"},{"type":"tags","id":"4989"},{"type":"tags","id":"4990"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5649"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11282"},{"type":"tags","id":"11296"},{"type":"tags","id":"11645"},{"type":"tags","id":"11648"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27236"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27242"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44852"},{"type":"contributions","id":"47402"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79657","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79657"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn anaesthetist develops progressive bilateral cataracts affecting their visual acuity. The condition impacts their ability to safely perform procedures requiring fine detail vision and depth perception. They have voluntarily restricted their practice to pre-operative consultations and no longer perform procedures. They are receiving treatment and engaging with regular ophthalmology review.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the mandatory reporting obligations in this situation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["No mandatory reporting required as risk is appropriately controlled","Must report to Medical Board due to visual impairment","Must report to employer but not Medical Board","Mandatory reporting required due to specialty","Must report if surgery is delayed"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct response is that \u003Cstrong\u003Eno mandatory reporting required as risk is appropriately controlled\u003C/strong\u003E. The practitioner has insight into their condition and has voluntarily restricted their practice to non-procedural work while engaging in treatment. Since they have implemented appropriate controls to mitigate risk, there is no substantial risk of harm to the public that would trigger mandatory reporting requirements.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMust report to Medical Board due to visual impairment\u003C/strong\u003E - The mere presence of an impairment does not trigger mandatory reporting if appropriate controls are in place\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMust report to employer but not Medical Board\u003C/strong\u003E - While good practice to inform employers of practice restrictions, this is not a mandatory reporting situation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMandatory reporting required due to specialty\u003C/strong\u003E - The specialty itself does not determine reporting requirements; the level of risk to public safety does\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMust report if surgery is delayed\u003C/strong\u003E - Timing of definitive treatment alone does not trigger reporting if other controls adequately mitigate risk\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe key consideration is whether there is a substantial risk of harm to the public, taking into account practice context, controls, and risk mitigation strategies. Impairment alone does not trigger mandatory reporting unless it places the public at a substantial risk of harm. In this case, appropriate measures have been implemented to protect patient safety.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Mandatory reporting is only required when a practitioner\u0027s impairment poses a substantial risk of harm to the public.","Practice modifications and treatment engagement can mitigate the need for mandatory reporting in cases of potential practitioner impairment.","Self-awareness and voluntary practice restrictions demonstrate appropriate professional insight."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx.","AHPRA and National Boards. Guidelines: Mandatory notifications about registered health practitioners [internet]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available from: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/guidelines-for-mandatory-notifications.aspx."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64961"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18839"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64961","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64961"},"attributes":{"created